&lt;p&gt;b4: add remark to phil comm: &lt;b&gt;a2.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;(kusne)...kotnaṣ&lt;/i&gt;: A TB parallel is to be found in [[THT 1102]] a2 &lt;i&gt;(śaultsa wä)rpoṣ pāssi&lt;/i&gt; and a TA parallel in [[A 64]] a2 &lt;i&gt;śolā pāssi wärporäṣ&lt;/i&gt; (cf. [[Schmidt KT 1986]]: 122). ?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Translation [[Ogihara 2009]]: 419:&lt;br&gt;
a1 /// thereby, one ought to accept to observe the moral behavior for whole life with the whole heart&lt;br&gt;
a2 /// (they abandon ... ). They put (their) life as debt. Like now, they enter into the battles. ...&lt;br&gt;
a3 /// it should be protected. Thereby this moral behavior ... the great ...&lt;br&gt;
a4 /// ... Say this! I, named thus, make Buddha as support. (I make) the law&lt;br&gt;
b1 /// I make (the community) as support. A third time, I make Buddha as support.&lt;br&gt;
b2 /// I made the community as suppport. Take me as male lay-disciple of that glorious one.&lt;br&gt;
b3 /// that has become (faithful). A second time, I, named thus, made Buddha as support. (I made) the law&lt;br&gt;
b4 /// who has accepted (to observe) the moral behavior for whole life, gone to the support, become faithful. A third time,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]]: 173 translates: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a1 Thereupon the śīla is to be received whole-heartedly and preserved throughout one's life. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a2 [They] will lay down life [itself] as a pledge. As they now enter into the battle(s) ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a3 [It] should be preserved. Therefore this śīla ... the great ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a4 Say! "I, [who am] called so-and-so, I shall make the Buddha [my] refuge [and] the dharma [my refuge]. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b1 I shall make (the dharma my refuge = a4). For the third time, I, who am called so-and-so, make the Buddha [my] refuge. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b2 Having made [the Buddha] [my] refuge [now] take me as an upāsaka of the bhagavat. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b3 [They] having become ... : For the second time, I, who am called so-and-so, having made the Buddha my refuge [and having made] the dharma [my refuge] ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b4 Having received the [śīla] [into my] protection for [my whole] life, [and] having entered the refuge, [and] having become "believeing", [I worship] thee. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br&gt;
&lt;p&gt;TEKST OGI nog niet vergeleken&lt;/p&gt;</item>
